{
  "texts": [
    "Usually, attention-based explanations are presented with visualizations such as heatmaps.",
    "What: input-internal, global How: post-hoc, specific, scores or text Probing typically involves training a classifier that takes the representations of the explained model and predicts some property (Belinkov, 2022), making it a post-hoc model-specific method.",
    "Typically, the predicted concept is a syntactic or semantic property (Adi et al., 2017; Conneau et al., 2018; Hewitt and Liang, 2019; Lepori and Mc-Coy, 2020; Ravichander et al., 2021; Antverg and Belinkov, 2022; Amini et al., 2023; Vulic et al., 2023).",
    "Probing methods usually answer questions of how extractable a property is from a representation or what knowledge a model encodes.",
    "Thus, it can globaly describe the input-internal mechanism."
  ]
}